                         USB_CTRL_SET_TIMEOUT);
   ```
   The function `usb_control_msg` is used to receive data from the USB device. It reads up to 2 bytes into the buffer pointed to by `data`.

3. **Error Handling**:
   ```c
   if (ret < 0) {
       dev_warn(dev, "Failed to get K90 initial mode (error %d).\n", ret);
       ret = -EIO;
       goto out;
   }
